text:
Prezentacja:
złote, zmętnione, piana bardzo obfita, drobna, długo się utrzymuje, pięknie koronkuje;
Aromat:
zdecydowany, białe, wytrawne wino, lekkie dzikie nuty, po zabełtaniu trochę pomarańczy i sporo spirytusu;
Odczucie:
treściwe, nasycenie wysokie, finisz winny, drożdżowy;
Smak:
pomarańcze, brzoskwinie w alkoholu, troszkę stajni i goryczka ziołowo-alkoholowa, po ogrzaniu wyraźny karmel;
Ogólnie:
całkiem dobre, ale alkohol można było dużo lepiej ukryć.

33cl bottle from Westholme Stores, Goring, rateing #3900. 
Pale gold with a ring of white head; yeasty aroma;
crisp and slightly tart taste with some pear fruit and spice, and a soft creamy texture;
the finish is long, smooth, and syrupy with some warming spice.
A pleasant Tripel, but I was expecting far more from this.

UPDATED: APR 1, 2013 Aroma: delicate but very nice fruity (not only citrus) aroma maybe a little floral, no alcohol (big plus considering the percentage); 
Appearance: golden, hazy, with small but nice and quite long-lasting white (a little creamy) head; Taste: almost perfect, quite bitter with a little sweetness, perfect match with the aroma, just a trace of alcohol; Palate: moderately full body, rather thin feel, plus average carbonation; long bitter finish;
Overall: nothing less (or more) than great beer. Recommended.

AROMA: caramel and flowers, yeasty esters, touch of bubblegum
APPEARANCE: hazy straw colour, head was thin but lasting, lacing was moderate;
TASTE: sweet with a bitter finish
PALATE: medium body, longish finish, slightly creamy, moderate carbonation;
OVERALL: good example of the best of the style
